Tony Okafor, Awka The Peoples Democratic Party has urged its members in the South-East to unite and win the 2021 Anambra State governorship election; to brighten the chances for the emergence of a President of Igbo extraction in 2023. Chairman of the PDP Board of Trustees, Senator Walid Jibrin, said this during a grand reception for the state PDP chairman, Ndubuisi Nwobu, in Awka, the Anambra State capital, on Saturday. The All Progressives Grand Alliance, has ruled the state since 2006. Jibrin said, “All hands must be on deck as next year’s gubernatorial election in Anambra state will determine the future of the state and the fate of Ndigbo in the Nigerian political structure.” In his address at the event, Nwobu promised that the party under his leadership was prepared to do the needful to ensure victory come 2022. He also assured all governorship aspirants of a level playing field when it was time to choose a candidate. Dignitaries who attended the event include Austin Umahi, Senator Ben Obi, Chief Josephine Anenih, Dr. Obiora Okonkwo, Chris Azubuogu, Dr Godwin Maduka, Valentine Ozigbo, amongst others. Copyright PUNCH.
